org.cougaar.core.service
Interface MessageTransportService

All Superinterfaces:
Service
All Known Implementing Classes:
MessageTransportServiceProxy, SingleNodeMTSProxy
public interface MessageTransportService
extends Service

This service is the node-level message transport that agents use to send and receive messages.

See Also:
for intra-agent message handling.

Method Detail

sendMessage

void sendMessage(Message m)
Ask MessageTransport to deliver a message (asynchronously). message.getTarget() names the destination. The client must be registered, otherwise the message will not be sent.

registerClient

void registerClient(MessageTransportClient client)
Register a client with MessageTransport. A client is any object which can receive Messages directed to it as the Target of a message.

unregisterClient

void unregisterClient(MessageTransportClient client)
Unregister a client with MessageTransport. No further sendMessage calls will be accepted, and any queued messages which aren't successfully delivered will be dropped.

flushMessages

java.util.List<Message> flushMessages()
Block until all queued messages have been sent (or dropped).

Returns:
The list of dropped messages (could be null).

getIdentifier

java.lang.String getIdentifier()
Returns:
the name of the entity that this MessageTransport represents. Will usually be the name of a node.

addressKnown

boolean addressKnown(MessageAddress a)
Returns:
true IFF the MessageAddress is known to the nameserver
